(* Kept OUT of the top-level ROOT because this session needs a PATCHED Isabelle.

   Minilang_Agent_Injector.thy's whole body is

       setup \<open>Sign.map_syn (K Syntax.empty_syntax)\<close>

   and `Sign.map_syn` does not exist in a stock Isabelle -- it is exported by
   my-better-isabelle-prover's `expose_map_syn` patch, which is in the `dev`
   category, not `user`.  my_better_isabelle_prover/README.md categorises this
   session by name: "`dev` -- needed only by developer/experiment infrastructure:
   Isa-REPL, and Isa-Mini's translator and AoA agent injector."

   The conda `isabelle` package applies the `user` category only, deliberately and
   for the same reason isabelle-repl is not published at all.  With this session
   still declared in the top-level ROOT -- which `isabelle components -u` exposes
   wholesale -- `isabelle build Minilang_Agent_Injector` fails for every user of
   the published package with

       *** Value or constructor (map_syn) has not been declared in structure Sign

   Measured: Isa-Mini release-conda run 29677250284, where Minilang and
   Minilang_Agent built cleanly and only this one failed.

   The .thy still ships, so anyone running a `--category all` Isabelle can use it:

       isabelle build -d . -d Agent/Injector Minilang_Agent_Injector

   Same treatment, and the same reasoning, as REPL/ROOT and Agent/AoA_REPL/ROOT. *)

session Minilang_Agent_Injector = Minilang_Agent +
  theories
    Minilang_Agent_Injector
